When a merchant chooses a fixed number of days, the merchant has an extra X days to fulfill (ship) orders, on top of the regular 5 days. When a merchant chooses a fixed date to fulfill by, the merchant has up to the chosen deadline to fulfill their orders.
Keywords you might encounter: CNY - Chinese New Year

Merchant Content - Payment Charge Error.name: Merchant Content - Payment Charge Error Messages
Merchant Content - Payment Charge Error.description: Payment charge system is for merchants to get charged for their campaigns or store registration fee, they can use UMPay, Payoneer and PayPal. This includes error messages that are shown to merchants if they put invalid messages, try to use invalid payment provider or get unexpected errors from payment charge providers.

Merchant Content - Expedited Payment Pol.name: Merchant Content - Expedited Payment Policy Notifications
Merchant Content - Expedited Payment Pol.description: These components inform the merchant that they are participating in an expedited payment program. For weekly payments, they highlight the importance of having Paypal/Payoneer as their provider to ensure payments are processed correctly.

Merchant Content - Restricted Product Pa.name: Merchant Content - Restricted Product Page
Merchant Content - Restricted Product Pa.description: This page is for the Product Authorization Page, which merchants can sell restricted products (e.g. food, pet food, medications, beverages, baby carriers, safty belts, etc.) in their local regions. In this page, merchants can apply for the restricted products they want to sell.

Merchant Content - Merchant Report Buyer.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Report Buyer Fraud Page
Merchant Content - Merchant Report Buyer.description: Reasons for merchants to select from when they are reporting buyer frauds.

Merchant Content - Transaction Item Unde.name: Merchant Content - Transaction Item Under Review Email
Merchant Content - Transaction Item Unde.description: The email that is sent to the merchant when an order is in under review state. Under review state means an order should not be fulfilled until fraud team finishes reviewing it.

Merchant Content - LTL Orders and Fulfil.name: Merchant Content - LTL Orders and Fulfillment Emails and Notifications
Merchant Content - LTL Orders and Fulfil.description: These are emails and notifications in the merchant dashboard that we send to merchants regarding LTL orders and fulfillment related events, such as, refunds, address changes, negligence warnings and orders not confirmed. LTL shorts for less-than-truckload, and is a term to indicate large parcel transportation that uses small freights, or specifically less than truckload transportation.

Merchant Content - Onboarding and Offboa.name: Merchant Content - Onboarding and Offboarding - Emails and Notifications
Merchant Content - Onboarding and Offboa.description: Emails and notifications that are sent to merchants during the onboarding and off-boarding process. Includes merchant information requests and disabled account notifications.

Merchant Content - Order Delivery Confir.name: Merchant Content - Order Delivery Confirmation Upload
Merchant Content - Order Delivery Confir.description: Merchants may upload delivery confirmation for orders (required for LTL orders). The helper saves or updates ther orders' delivery confirmations. Error messages will be generated once missing fields are found.

Merchant Content - CSV Fulfillment Error.name: Merchant Content - CSV Fulfillment Errors
Merchant Content - CSV Fulfillment Error.description: Errors that the merchant may encounter when they attempt to fulfill orders via CSV

Merchant Content - Orders and Fulfillmen.name: Merchant Content - Orders and Fulfillment Emails and Notifications
Merchant Content - Orders and Fulfillmen.description: These are emails and notifications in the merchant dashboard that we send to merchants regarding orders and fulfillment related events, such as, refunds, address changes, negligence warnings and orders not confirmed.

Merchant Content - Order CSV Fulfillment.name: Merchant Content - Order CSV Fulfillment
Merchant Content - Order CSV Fulfillment.description: The required and optional columns that merchants need to supply when they fulfill orders with a CSV file.

Merchant Content - Transaction History P.name: Merchant Content - Transaction History Page
Merchant Content - Transaction History P.description: This page includes the banner of the transaction history page. Merchants see this on order history page. This banner includes the Transaction History title, as well as links to inform merchants how to increase sales.

Merchant Content - Marketplace - analyti.name: Merchant Content - Marketplace - analytics
Merchant Content - Marketplace - analyti.description: Strings used to display texts used in various dashboard statistical graphs and tables

Merchant Content - Merchant Sub-Accounts.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Sub-Accounts
Merchant Content - Merchant Sub-Accounts.description: Merchants are allowed to create accounts for their employees and team members so they can work together on Merchant Dashboard. This job contains content and error messages that may appear when they attempt to create sub-accounts.

Merchant Content - Fulfillment Reminder.name: Merchant Content - Fulfillment Reminder Email Notification
Merchant Content - Fulfillment Reminder.description: Email sent to merchants, to remind that they have new orders to fulfill in certain days, along with instructions on providing valid tracking information, policy without providing tracking information, and FAQs.

Merchant Content - PayPal Error Emails.name: Merchant Content - PayPal Error Emails
Merchant Content - PayPal Error Emails.description: Emails sent to merchants, providing them suggestions to solve PayPal account issues

Merchant Content - Authentication Settin.name: Merchant Content - Authentication Settings Errors
Merchant Content - Authentication Settin.description: Strings sent to merchants detailing errors and results when they try to edit settings related to authentication.

Merchant Content - Merchant Store Review.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Store Review
Merchant Content - Merchant Store Review.description: Most merchants are required to submit their store for review before their products may become live on Wish.com. Content in this job included error message and shown to the merchant when they attempt to submit their stores.

Merchant Content - Device Settings Error.name: Merchant Content - Device Settings Errors
Merchant Content - Device Settings Error.description: Strings sent to merchants detailing errors and results when they try to remove devices from their account.

Merchant Content - Accepted Shipping Pro.name: Merchant Content - Accepted Shipping Providers Page
Merchant Content - Accepted Shipping Pro.description: Pages displaying the details of restrictions for the qualified shipping providers

Merchant Content - Shipping Settings Err.name: Merchant Content - Shipping Settings Error
Merchant Content - Shipping Settings Err.description: Error messages that appear the the merchant when they attempt to edit their shipping settings.

Merchant Content - Merchant Charging Acc.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Charging Account Page
Merchant Content - Merchant Charging Acc.description: This page is used to charge merchants for ProductBoost. It includes payment information and instructions that guide merchants to pay for ProductBoost step by step

Merchant Content - EPC Tracking Status.name: Merchant Content - EPC Tracking Status
Merchant Content - EPC Tracking Status.description: Pages displaying tracking status of EPC order. EPC (Export Package Combination) is a fulfillment program provided by wish for faster delivery and reduced costs.

Merchant Content - Customer Support Tool.name: Merchant Content - Customer Support Tool
Merchant Content - Customer Support Tool.description: Customer Support tool pages used by merchants and agents to reply and solve customer support tickets

Merchant Content - Merchant Ticket Notif.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Ticket Notifications
Merchant Content - Merchant Ticket Notif.description: Emails and in app notifications sent to merchants regarding when a customer has contacted them by creating a support ticket

Merchant Content - Ticket Handle Privile.name: Merchant Content - Ticket Handle Privilege Program
Merchant Content - Ticket Handle Privile.description: The Customer Support Privilege program is a program which grants extra permissions to merchants to provide customer support. For example, merchants in the program can respond to customer's tickets.

Merchant Content - Counterfeit Policy Pa.name: Merchant Content - Counterfeit Policy Page
Merchant Content - Counterfeit Policy Pa.description: The counterfeit policies are the policies about intellectual property rules at Wish. This page contains the links to the details of the counterfeit policies, and the consequences of violating the policies.

Merchant Content - Brand University.name: Merchant Content - Brand University
Merchant Content - Brand University.description: Information for merchants about Wish's Intellectual Property rules.

Merchant Content - Counterfeit Resource.name: Merchant Content - Counterfeit Resource Centre
Merchant Content - Counterfeit Resource.description: Resources to help merchants identify counterfeit products and avoid them.

Merchant Content - Brand Authorization.name: Merchant Content - Brand Authorization
Merchant Content - Brand Authorization.description: Merchant facing legacy pages and email templates for brand authorization.

Merchant Content - V3 API Explorer.name: Merchant Content - V3 API Explorer
Merchant Content - V3 API Explorer.description: An user-friendly web app for people to test and play around with V3 API endpoints. Users can easily generate requests by filling out inputs and see corresponding responses on the same page.

Merchant Content - External Api Release.name: Merchant Content - External Api Release Notes
Merchant Content - External Api Release.description: A page where we share updates of our API to partners with a change history. For example, information about changes to the format of API requests/responses, changes to what errors might be returned, description/naming changes. Strings will be displayed in separate categories according to their version, type of change and where its being changed.

Merchant Content - ERP Signup Page.name: Merchant Content - ERP Signup Page
Merchant Content - ERP Signup Page.description: A signup page for people who want to become partners with Wish and develop software and tools that support our merchants. On this specific page, one would expect a list of forms for the user to fill out. After this page, their signup will be approved by someone.

Merchant Content - Partner Developer Pag.name: Merchant Content - Partner Developer Page
Merchant Content - Partner Developer Pag.description: A landing page with information for partners wanting to use our API. We'd expect this page to have details about documentation, tutorials, FAQ. This page will also show off successful partners to attract new partners to sign up.

Merchant Content - Brand Partner.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner
Merchant Content - Brand Partner.description: Strings used for Brand Partner related pages and APIs, such as the Brand Partner landing and signup pages, and email templates used in communicating with approved brand partners. Regarding's Wish's intellectual property policy, do not communicate that it is zero-tolerance.

Merchant Content - Product Listing Revie.name: Merchant Content - Product Listing Review Status
Merchant Content - Product Listing Revie.description: Strings for displaying product review status, e.g. Approved, Rejected.

Merchant Content - API Base.name: Merchant Content - API Base
Merchant Content - API Base.description: Foundation of all API calls we make to merchants. Mostly consists of technical error messages describing issues to API users.

Merchant Content - Branded Products.name: Merchant Content - Branded Products
Merchant Content - Branded Products.description: Pages related to branded products, including the Brand Directory and the Authentic Brand Seller Application. Brand Directory allows merchants to view a list of the brands they can tag their products with on Wish, and provides a screen for them to request Wish to add new brands, as well as a page for them to see the status of their existing and historical brand requests. Authentic Brand Seller provide a channel for merchants to validate their authorization status for a brand, as well as a list of such applications they have submitted in the past.

Merchant Content - Account Settings - Er.name: Merchant Content - Account Settings - Error Messages
Merchant Content - Account Settings - Er.description: A series of error messages that user may see when they attempt to update their account settings.

Merchant Content - Merchant invite frien.name: Merchant Content - Merchant invite friends
Merchant Content - Merchant invite frien.description: Allow merchants to invite friends to sell on Wish. And for each friend who uploads more than 10 products, we will issue the inviter $100 PB credit.

Merchant Content - Merchant Currency.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Currency
Merchant Content - Merchant Currency.description: Pages and services that merchants can use to, view their current currency, as well as requesting changes to the currency. All rates should be refering to exchange rates.

Merchant Content - Email Base.name: Merchant Content - Email Base
Merchant Content - Email Base.description: Foundation of all emails we send to merchants. Includes common greetings and disclaimers, unsubscribe links etc.

Merchant Content - Account Settings Page.name: Merchant Content - Account Settings Page
Merchant Content - Account Settings Page.description: Contents that appear in account settings page

Merchant Content - Third Party Ethics Ho.name: Merchant Content - Third Party Ethics Hotline Page
Merchant Content - Third Party Ethics Ho.description: The page displays information of third party ethics hotline. The hotline is created so that third parties, such as logistics providers, can raise ethics concerns to Wish, either anonymously or with their name attached. Wish wants to conduct its business ethically and in accordance with applicable law, and we count on our third parties to let us know if we are not meeting those standards.

Merchant Content - Error Pages.name: Merchant Content - Error Pages
Merchant Content - Error Pages.description: Error pages display to the user when something goes wrong with the page they've requested. Examples are "Page not found", "Permission Denied", "Internal error".

Merchant Content - Announcements - Categ.name: Merchant Content - Announcements - Category and Program Names
Merchant Content - Announcements - Categ.description: Categories are a subset of the tags that the user can use to filter and organize announcements into different groupings. Programs are the different initiatives that we offer at Wish for our merchants to enhance their impressions and sales.

Merchant Content - EPC - Order.name: Merchant Content - EPC - Order
Merchant Content - EPC - Order.description: Pages and modals related to EPC/A+ orders, such as removing order from A+. EPC(Export Package Combination)/A+(advanced logistics) are fulfillment programs provided by wish for faster delivery and reduced costs.

Merchant Content - Announcements - Syste.name: Merchant Content - Announcements - System Updates
Merchant Content - Announcements - Syste.description: Displays a list of System Updates sent to the user, sorted by recency. System Updates are announcements that contain relevant information on policies, features, logistics, or other pertinent updates with information that we want the user to be aware of.

Merchant Content - Orders - Shipping Doc.name: Merchant Content - Orders - Shipping Documentation
Merchant Content - Orders - Shipping Doc.description: Provides merchants with documentation about available shipping carriers and which carriers are preferred and allowed in different countries.

Merchant Content - Signup Login Authenti.name: Merchant Content - Signup Login Authentication Error Messages
Merchant Content - Signup Login Authenti.description: A series of errors message that could be shown to the user when they attempt to log in or signup for "Wish for Merchants".

Merchant Content - Merchant Review Compo.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Review Components
Merchant Content - Merchant Review Compo.description: Pages related to the review of merchants immediately after signup, or re-authentication of merchants sometime afterward.

Merchant Content - SMS and Phone Calls.name: Merchant Content - SMS and Phone Calls
Merchant Content - SMS and Phone Calls.description: Templates for SMS and automated phone calls sent by Merchant Dashboard to merchants, plus system messages for SMS/phone call errors

Merchant Content - Shipping Setting Page.name: Merchant Content - Shipping Setting Page
Merchant Content - Shipping Setting Page.description: Pages and features related to Shipping Setting

Merchant Content - Product Listing Polic.name: Merchant Content - Product Listing Policy Page
Merchant Content - Product Listing Polic.description: Pages related to the product listing restrictions, and merchant-facing texts for inappropriate and counterfeit tagging.

Merchant Content - Home Page.name: Merchant Content - Home Page
Merchant Content - Home Page.description: Content that appears on a merchant's home page

Merchant Content - Wish Express - Error.name: Merchant Content - Wish Express - Error Messages
Merchant Content - Wish Express - Error.description: Error messages from the Wish Express API.

Merchant Content - Wechat store pages.name: Merchant Content - Wechat store pages
Merchant Content - Wechat store pages.description: These apis provides data to the WeChat store app. This means merchants are able to access their store info through the WeChat directly.

Merchant Content - FBS - Performance Pag.name: Merchant Content - FBS - Performance Page
Merchant Content - FBS - Performance Pag.description: The page provides aggregated and granular sales data for the Fulfilled by Store Program (GMV (Gross Merchandise Value), orders, etc). Merchants can view sales data for different date ranges among their various products.

Merchant Content - Product Upload and Ed.name: Merchant Content - Product Upload and Edit Error and Success Messages
Merchant Content - Product Upload and Ed.description: These are the core pathways merchants use to edit and upload their products. Most strings will be explicit error messages, warnings or success messages.

Merchant Content - Re-authentication Pag.name: Merchant Content - Re-authentication Pages
Merchant Content - Re-authentication Pag.description: Pages related to re-authentication flow. Current there are 2 situations where merchats are put into this flow. 1. When we suspect their accounts are taken over by hackers, they have to go through this flow to recover their account. 2. When they have invalid registration information, they have to go through this flow to fix their registration information.

Merchant Content - Payment Creation Erro.name: Merchant Content - Payment Creation Errors
Merchant Content - Payment Creation Erro.description: These are the emails that will be sent to the merchants during payment creation when errors occur and need to inform merchants

Merchant Content - Product Upload and Ed.name: Merchant Content - Product Upload and Edits Pages
Merchant Content - Product Upload and Ed.description: Pages related to products, uploads and edits

Merchant Content - Payment Detail Modal.name: Merchant Content - Payment Detail Modal
Merchant Content - Payment Detail Modal.description: It is the modal we show to merchant from order history page and order detail page It contains information related to order's payment details including payment amount breakdown, payment eligibility, available payment date, refunds and penalties

Merchant Content - Merchant Early Paymen.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Early Payments
Merchant Content - Merchant Early Paymen.description: Feature for Early Payments. Includes wording to indicate important dates, payment amounts, and confirmation of agreement to terms of service. learn more about early payments here: https://merchantfaq.wish.com/hc/en-us/articles/360043372513

Merchant Content - Wishpost Settings.name: Merchant Content - Wishpost Settings
Merchant Content - Wishpost Settings.description: Page where merchants can edit their Wishpost settings. Wishpost is a custom shipping carrier for merchants shipping out of China.

Merchant Content - Payments - Uncategori.name: Merchant Content - Payments - Uncategorized
Merchant Content - Payments - Uncategori.description: Pages and features related to Payments

Merchant Content - Payment Holds.name: Merchant Content - Payment Holds
Merchant Content - Payment Holds.description: A payment hold (block on payments) is put on a merchant's account so that the merchant is not paid for a certain time period (until the hold is removed from the account). These files contain strings related to these payment holds and how they impact merchants.

Merchant Content - FBW - Usage Fees.name: Merchant Content - FBW - Usage Fees
Merchant Content - FBW - Usage Fees.description: This page lists out the fees the merchant will be charged for the Fulfilled by Wish program

Merchant Content - Payments Account Bala.name: Merchant Content - Payments Account Balance
Merchant Content - Payments Account Bala.description: Pages and features related to payments account balance

Merchant Content - FBS - Usage Fees.name: Merchant Content - FBS - Usage Fees
Merchant Content - FBS - Usage Fees.description: This page lists out the fees the merchant will be charged for the Fulfilled by Store program

Merchant Content - FBW - Create Wish Loc.name: Merchant Content - FBW - Create Wish Local Shipping Plans
Merchant Content - FBW - Create Wish Loc.description: This page allows Wish Local merchants to create shipping plans for the Fulfilled By Wish program

Merchant Content - FBW Uncategorized.name: Merchant Content - FBW Uncategorized
Merchant Content - FBW Uncategorized.description: Miscellaneous strings related to FBW (Fulfill By Wish, which is a program that allows the merchant to ship their products in advance to our warehouses, thus giving customers faster shipping speed when they place orders), including merchant management tools page strings, invoice page strings and localized API response messages.

Merchant Content - FBS - Inventory List.name: Merchant Content - FBS - Inventory List
Merchant Content - FBS - Inventory List.description: This page provides inventory quantity for each warehouse on the product and SKU level, also allows the merchant to set shipping price for the Fulfilled by Store program

Merchant Content - FBW - Shipping Plan H.name: Merchant Content - FBW - Shipping Plan History
Merchant Content - FBW - Shipping Plan H.description: This page provides shipping plan history for Fulfilled By Wish products

Merchant Content - FBS - Fee Structure.name: Merchant Content - FBS - Fee Structure
Merchant Content - FBS - Fee Structure.description: This page provides fee structure information on Fulfilled by Store program

Merchant Content - FBW - Inventory List.name: Merchant Content - FBW - Inventory List
Merchant Content - FBW - Inventory List.description: This page provides inventory quantity for each warehouse on the product and SKU level, also allows the merchant to set shipping price for the Fulfilled by Wish program

Merchant Content - FBW - Create FBW Ship.name: Merchant Content - FBW - Create FBW Shipping Plan Page
Merchant Content - FBW - Create FBW Ship.description: This page allows the merchant to select and send their products to Fulfilled By Wish Warehouses in the US and EU. Here, SKU is the standard abbreviation for "Stock Keeping Unit", and GMV is the standard abbreviation for "Gross Merchandise Value"

Merchant Content - FBW - Shipping Plan L.name: Merchant Content - FBW - Shipping Plan List
Merchant Content - FBW - Shipping Plan L.description: This page allows the merchant view their Fulfilled By Wish shipping plans.

Merchant Content - FBW FBS - Recommendat.name: Merchant Content - FBW FBS - Recommendation Dashboard
Merchant Content - FBW FBS - Recommendat.description: The page provides recommendations (top variations, drop shipping price, low in stock products) to merchants in the Fulfilled by Wish/Fulfilled by Store program The email is sent to merchants to show recommended products.

Merchant Content - FBW - Performance Das.name: Merchant Content - FBW - Performance Dashboard
Merchant Content - FBW - Performance Das.description: The page provides aggregated and granular sales data for the Fulfilled by Wish Program(GMV (Gross Merchandise Value), orders, etc).

Merchant Content - FBW - Warehouse Fee P.name: Merchant Content - FBW - Warehouse Fee Page
Merchant Content - FBW - Warehouse Fee P.description: Pages displaying the fees charged for the Fulfilled By Wish program

Merchant Content - Merchant Fine Details.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Fine Details Page
Merchant Content - Merchant Fine Details.description: pages related a single fine details

Merchant Content - Infraction View Page.name: Merchant Content - Infraction View Page
Merchant Content - Infraction View Page.description: Infractions are the warnings Wish creates for merchants to notify them their violation of Wish merchant policies and what corresponding fine/ban punishments are applied. Infractions also inform merchants what actions should they take to avoid the fine/ban punishments.

Merchant Content - Potential Merchant Em.name: Merchant Content - Potential Merchant Emails and Unsubscribe
Merchant Content - Potential Merchant Em.description: Email templates for potential merchants (merchant leads), and a way to unsubscribe a recipient from said emails

Merchant Content - Unification Initiativ.name: Merchant Content - Unification Initiative
Merchant Content - Unification Initiativ.description: The Unification Initiative is a program that changes the way that Wish pays China merchants for shipping for certain orders. Previously, Wish would reimburse merchants for A+ orders based on the shipping price that the merchant inputted into the system. With the new initiative, merchants will be able to specify their own price for First Mile Shipping for A+ orders, and Wish will reimburse the merchant the exact price that the merchant paid WishPost to ship the order.

Merchant Content - Norway VAT.name: Merchant Content - Norway VAT
Merchant Content - Norway VAT.description: This page provides explanations to merchants about the requirement on shipping label for Norway VAT orders

Merchant Content - Merchant Set Fulfillm.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Set Fulfillment Extension
Merchant Content - Merchant Set Fulfillm.description: The error messages related to setting fulfillment extensions on merchant level. Fulfillment extension means that merchant has extra time to fulfill their orders.

Merchant Content - Package Overview Page.name: Merchant Content - Package Overview Page
Merchant Content - Package Overview Page.description: This page provides the package overview of a given order. It includes customer pricing, shipping and tax information.

Merchant Content - Returns - Uncategoriz.name: Merchant Content - Returns - Uncategorized
Merchant Content - Returns - Uncategoriz.description: Pages and features related to Merchant Returns. Merchants can enroll individual products in the returns program. When a customer wants to return an enrolled product and get a refund, the customer must now print off a return shipping label and ship the product to the warehouse that the merchant specifies. Once the product reaches the specified warehouse, the customer will be refunded. These pages include the UI for merchants to enroll products, set up return warehouses, learn more about returns, and carry out other tasks related to returns.

Merchant Content - Order Detail Page.name: Merchant Content - Order Detail Page
Merchant Content - Order Detail Page.description: This page provides full details about an order to the merchant. It includes customer shipping information, product details, penalties, tracking, tax information and other order-related attributes.

Merchant Content - Order External API.name: Merchant Content - Order External API
Merchant Content - Order External API.description: Order external APIs is a set of APIs relating to the following: - ship, refund an order - modify tracking, update address for an order - Texts here include: - error messages related to improper usage of a certain API endpoint - these errors are due to improper parameter passing and/or attempts to perform unauthorized actions or actions that cannot be done given the state of the data - messages to indicate errors for a specific field

Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Uncateg.name: Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Uncategorized
Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Uncateg.description: Pages and features related to order fulfillment

Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Mark Sh.name: Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Mark Shipped and Modify Tracking Business Logic Error Messages
Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Mark Sh.description: When a merchant marks shipped an order or modifies tracking of an order, we do some validation on the inputs. This grouping contains various error messages that we might surface to the merchant if some validation fails.

Merchant Content - Disputes.name: Merchant Content - Disputes
Merchant Content - Disputes.description: Disputes are a process in which merchants can appeal penalties issued against their orders or account. A Wish admin will review the appeal and decide whether to reject or accept the dispute.

Merchant Content - Fine Policies Page.name: Merchant Content - Fine Policies Page
Merchant Content - Fine Policies Page.description: Penalties are issued when your products, orders or your store violated Wish policies. This page presents a list of Wish penalties.

Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Mark Sh.name: Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Mark Shipped UI
Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Mark Sh.description: Pages and features related to order fulfillment UI. These files contain some of the text that is visible to merchants when they are marking orders as shipped or modifying tracking information of shipped orders.

Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Unfulfi.name: Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Unfulfilled Order Policy
Merchant Content - Fulfillment - Unfulfi.description: Internally also called the Auto-Refund Policy. Policy where orders must be Marked Shipped within a certain number of days (usually 5) or the order will be auto-refunded. Merchant may also receive a fine + suspensions.

Merchant Content - Notifications.name: Merchant Content - Notifications
Merchant Content - Notifications.description: Merchant notifications are our way to let the user know about important announcements, messages, or events in one centralized place.

Merchant Content - Merchant TRO.name: Merchant Content - Merchant TRO
Merchant Content - Merchant TRO.description: Merchant Injunctions tools on Merchant Dashboard. This flow is to speed up TRO process between merchant and court. A TRO, in the context of e-commerce, is to stop sellers from listing trademarked goods on their platforms.

Merchant Content - Merchant Payment Down.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Payment Download Jobs
Merchant Content - Merchant Payment Down.description: For generating a spreadsheet containing merchants' payment related info (order, fines, fees, hold, etc.) and emailing the download link to the merchants or PSP.

Merchant Content - Delivered Duty Paid -.name: Merchant Content - Delivered Duty Paid - DDP
Merchant Content - Delivered Duty Paid -.description: For high-priced Germany-bound orders, merchants need to use qualified shipping carriers that support paying Value Added (VAT) on their behalf. The tax is called "Delivered Duty".

Merchant Content - Merchant Payment Serv.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Payment Service Provider - AllPay
Merchant Content - Merchant Payment Serv.description: Disbursement util methods related to AllPay, which is one of Merchant Payment Service Providers. These util methods are for synchronizing AllPay payment status, marking succeed/failed status of AllPay payments, submitting AllPay payment, etc.

Merchant Content - Transaction List Page.name: Merchant Content - Transaction List Page
Merchant Content - Transaction List Page.description: This page shows the transaction list to merchants. Merchants see this list on order history page as well as action required page, where they can view details of orders or take actions

Merchant Content - Download Jobs.name: Merchant Content - Download Jobs
Merchant Content - Download Jobs.description: For generating a spreadsheet containing merchants' info (fines, fees, etc.) and emailing the download link to the merchants.

Merchant Content - Site Navigation.name: Merchant Content - Site Navigation
Merchant Content - Site Navigation.description: Content that appears in site navigation -- the top bar on the site as well as the site footer, sitemap etc.

Merchant Content - Signup Page.name: Merchant Content - Signup Page
Merchant Content - Signup Page.description: Signup and onboarding process on Merchant Dashboard, for both Chinese and non-Chinese merchants

Merchant Content - Uncategorized Legacy.name: Merchant Content - Uncategorized Legacy
Merchant Content - Uncategorized Legacy.description: Dump of uncategorized files from legacy code.

Merchant Content - UI Core.name: Merchant Content - UI Core
Merchant Content - UI Core.description: 'UI Core consists of: - A set of reusable user interface components: buttons, tables alerts, forms, country-pickers, date pickers, etc. These building blocks are used to build features on merchant dashboard. - Error messages describing problems to users on the merchant dashboard web interface'

Merchant Content - Price Drop Download R.name: Merchant Content - Price Drop Download Records
Merchant Content - Price Drop Download R.description: Generate Price Drop Records asynchronously and send out email notification with the download link.

Merchant Content - Merchant Standing.name: Merchant Content - Merchant Standing
Merchant Content - Merchant Standing.description: 'The Merchant Standing program aims to motivate merchants to care and learn about their current store status and how they can improve. Merchants are categorized into four categories: Under Review, Active, Silver, Gold, Platinum. Based on their standing merchants will be rewarded with additional impressions.'

Merchant Content - Todo List.name: Merchant Content - Todo List
Merchant Content - Todo List.description: Todo lists allow merchants to track action items that they need to perform on Merchant Dashboard. We surface action items that the merchant needs to complete.

Merchant Content - Home Banner.name: Merchant Content - Home Banner
Merchant Content - Home Banner.description: Home banners appear vividly at the top of a merchant's home page. This slide-based banner surfaces marketing material from wish, or new programs that the we want to inform the merchants about.

Merchant Content - Seller Profile Verifi.name: Merchant Content - Seller Profile Verification Flow
Merchant Content - Seller Profile Verifi.description: When sales of merchants reaches a threshold, and if they didn't provide real-name information, They need to go through this flow to provide the real-name information

Merchant Content - External Apps.name: Merchant Content - External Apps
Merchant Content - External Apps.description: 'Apps are applications (such as ERPs) built by partners that integrate with Merchant Dashboard. Especially, Private apps are custom third party apps that merchants can integrate with merchant dashboard." Texts here include: - App related emails - App related front-end components'

Merchant Content - Customer Service Perf.name: Merchant Content - Customer Service Performance Page
Merchant Content - Customer Service Perf.description: Overview of various metrics which show how well a merchant is serving their customers. For example, number of refunds, customer satisfaction ratings, etc.

Merchant Content - Login Page.name: Merchant Content - Login Page
Merchant Content - Login Page.description: Content that appears in the login page on Merchant Dashboard.

Merchant Content - KYC Verification Flow.name: Merchant Content - KYC Verification Flow

Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 - Em.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 - Emails
Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 - Em.description:
A email sent to the user upon the creation of a Brand Partner account, brands, and takedown requests along with any status updates of them. It also contains generic email-related text such as "unsubcribe from emails".
The Brand Partner Program allows brands to register their trademarks and logos and submit takedown requests for counterfeit products. Eventually, the program will encourage Brand Partners to register as merchants as well.

Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 UI C.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 UI Core
Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 UI C.description: Shared UI widgets used for the Brand Partner V2 Project

Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Home.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Home Page
Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Home.description: The home page for the Brand Partner V2 Project. This contains a welcoming text for the  user as well as titles and descriptions for features.

Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Veri.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Verify Email Pages
Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Veri.description: These pages request the user to verify their email. Users will be allowed to re-request a verification email or change their email.

Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Land.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Landing Page
Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Land.description: Landing Page for the Brand Partner V2 Project. This includes text about the Brand Partner Program, such as a description of the program, the advantages of signing up, and a rough outline of the onboarding steps. Also includes text for the navigation header of the landing page, which contains the header text "Brand Partner", and text for the login and signup links and buttons.

Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Logi.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Login Page
Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Logi.description: Login Page for the Brand Partner V2 Project. This contains text describing the email and password fields and error messages for when the user has entered incorrect details. This also contains text and error messages for two-factor authentication.

Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Site.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Site Footer
Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Site.description: The site footer of the Brand Partner V2 Project contains text describing internal links within Wish, such as FAQ, Terms of Service, and Privacy Policy. It also provides text for a "Contact Us" link.

Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Acco.name: Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Account Recovery Pages
Merchant Content - Brand Partner V2 Acco.description: These pages allow the user to reset their password with an email link, if they have  forgotten it.
